Instead, use `DockerReference()` to obtain the repository name (which also makes it work for other transports that support Docker references), and a check for `docker.Transport` + the newly introduced `docker.GetRepositoryTags`.

This will allow dropping `docker.Image` from `containers/image`, and maybe even all of `ImageReference.NewImage` (forcing callers to think about manifest lists, among other things).

@runcom PTAL (non-urgent), primarly WDYT about eventually dropping the `NewImage` interface and forcing callers to deal with `ImageSource` and `image.FromSource` / `FromUnparsedImage` themselves? Or maybe wrap that in something like `c/image/image.FromReference(types.ImageReference)` so that callers continue to need only one call instead of two?
